commit.message:
Merge pull request #11 from kohsuke/master

improving error diagnosis.

improving error diagnosis.

This is done to better understand reported problems such as https://issues.jenkins-ci.org/browse/JENKINS-20618 and https://issues.jenkins-ci.org/browse/JENKINS-20114 where jzlib can be seen mysteriously failing.
JUnit will not be used anymore.

ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException in Tree.d_code
  * https://github.com/ymnk/jzlib/issues/9
  * fixed a bug in calculating the size of the pending buffer.
  * added a test case based on https://github.com/jglick/jzlib-9-demo
ScalaTest should be used instead of JUnit.
Inflater with DEF_WBITS+32 should accept zlib and gzip data.

HeaderType is renamed as WraperType.

The date will have a header and a trailer, so WrapperType must be better.
new Inflater(W_GZIP) should fail for the deflated data with zlib-header.
In case W_ANY for nowrap mode, avail_in and total_in should be also updated.

inflater should be able to detect the format of deflated data.

  * an enum type JZlib.WrapperType is added.
      JZlib.W_NONE
      JZlib.W_ZLIB
      JZlib.W_GZIP
      JZlib.W_ANY

  * Inflater with JZlib.W_ANY can inflate any deflated data
    even if it has zlib header or gzip header or no-header.

  * Deflate can easily generate zlib-ed data, gzip-ed data or nowrap data
    with a WrapperyType parameter.

  * following methods are added,
    ZStream#inflateInit(JZlib.WrapperType)
    ZStream#inflateInit(int, JZlib.WrapperType)
    ZStream#deflateInit(int, int, int, JZlib.WrapperType)

  * refer following test for how-to specify Wrappertype,
    src/test/scala/WrapperTypeTest.scala
new Inflater() should not throw an exception.

issue7: contention on static synchronized gen_codes() under high load
